Description: Three views of Egypt in overlap; at left, a camp under palm trees, with arabs, one riding a camel; at centre, busy street in Cairo; at right, scene on the bank of the Nile with figures and boats; proof illustration to 'The Illustrated London News'; after Georges Montbard. Wood-engraving
Producer name: Print made by: William Michael Roberts Quick
Acquisition name: Donated by: William Michael Roberts Quick
